Git and Github is version control system.
It address the problem of sharing codes created by differnet devlopers for common project.
Next problem it addresses is of versioning like if one wants to go back to 50 days back code piece.
Git is a distributed version control system.It is a opensource thing.
What is fork?->It is a copy of original source.
Everything in git is tracked as objects.
Using hooks we can prevent mistakes like that of api token.
Git status->tells about current repositry status.It checks if there is an untracked file in it or not.
git add with file name tracks the file.
git diff->tells what exact changes have been maded
